<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>On Favoritism...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Thorim">Thorim</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:25 a.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> On Favoritism...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I've read a lot of posts clamouring about 'favoritism' by GM's in Everquest.

<P>While I certainly hope that we will never see any favoritism, it is certainly possible that it could crop up, in which case we definately need to deal with it.
<P>If you observe something that you feel was favoritism by any of the guide staff, PLEASE contact the Senior Guide on your server (that is Abashi on the PvP server), or one of the other Senior Guides such as myself.
<P>Please provide a clear, reasoned report on what actions you observed, when, and where, and the names of the people and staff involved.
<P>Favortism is not, and will not, be condoned or allowed in Everquest, that is one of our foremost precepts.
<P>Thorim
<BR>Senior Guide, Everquest
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
